@startuml PAR Flow
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

actor       User   as user
participant Browser as browser
participant "Demo Backend" as be
participant "MAB API" as mab
participant "ETSI Sign API" as etsi

== Step 1 – PAR Auth ==

user -> browser: Upload PDF, select journey
browser -> be++: **POST /api/par/auth**\n(multipart: pdf, journey)
note right of be
  Prepare PDF (PDFBox):
  - add signature placeholder
  - compute byte range
  - SHA-256 hash digest
end note
be -> mab++: **POST parUri** (mTLS)\nCreateParRequest
mab --> be--: ParResponse
note right of be
  Build authorization URL
  GET {authorizationUri}
  ?request_uri=...&client_id=...
end note
be --> browser--: ParStartResponse
browser -> browser : Display auth link

== Step 2 – User Authentication ==

user -> browser : Click "Open QTSP Auth"
browser -> mab++: Open authorizationUrl in new tab
user -> mab : Complete authentication
mab --> browser--: Redirect to redirect_uri\n?code=...&state=...
user -> browser : Paste authorization code

== Step 3 – Token Exchange ==

user -> browser : Click "Exchange Token"
browser -> be++: **POST /api/par/token**\nParTokenExchangeRequest
note right of be
  Validate session (state + nonce)
end note
be -> mab++: **POST tokenUri** (mTLS)\nAuthorizationCodeTokenRequest
mab --> be--: TokenResponse
be --> browser--: TokenExchangeResponse

== Step 4 – ETSI Sign ==

user -> browser : Click "Call ETSI Sign"
browser -> be++: **POST /api/etsi/sign**\nEtsiSignStartRequest
note right of be
  Retrieve session with SAD JWT
  Parse JWT aud → ETSI endpoint
end note
be -> etsi++: **POST etsiSignUri** (mTLS)\nEtsiSignRequest
etsi --> be--: EtsiSignResponse
note right of be
  Embed CMS into PDF
  Upgrade to PAdES B-LT (LTV)
end note
be --> browser--: EtsiSignStartResponse
user -> browser : Click "Download PDF"

@enduml

